This paper deals with privacy issues in the context of programmatic advertising, which is a topic that falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also involves data analysis and privacy-preserving techniques, which are relevant to information retrieval (cs.IR) and database systems (cs.DB). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of a browser extension, which falls under the category of social and information networks (cs.SI). Finally, the paper touches on the topic of privacy in cyberspace, which is relevant to the category of computers and society (cs.CY).
